**Idea:**

This is the most efficient method to find articulation points in a connected, undirected graph. The algorithm performs a depth-first search (DFS) and maintains two arrays for each vertex:


**Discovery time,** tin[u]tin[u]tin[u]: the time at which vertex uuu is first visited.
**Low value,** low[u]low[u]low[u]: the smallest discovery time reachable from uuu (including uuu itself) through any of its descendants, possibly using a back edge.
As we traverse the graph:


For each vertex uuu, we iterate over its neighbors. If the neighbor vvv has not yet been visited, we recursively call DFS on it.
After the DFS call, we update low[u]low[u]low[u] with low[v]low[v]low[v].
For a non-root vertex uuu, if for any child vvv in the DFS tree we have
low[v]≥tin[u],low[v] \ge tin[u],low[v]≥tin[u],
then uuu is an articulation point.
For the root of the DFS, if it has more than one child, then it is an articulation point.
**Why It Works:**

The lowlowlow value indicates if a subtree has a “back edge” that connects to an ancestor of uuu. When for a child vvv, low[v]≥tin[u]low[v] \ge tin[u]low[v]≥tin[u], it means no such back edge exists, and removal of uuu would disconnect the component containing vvv from the rest of the graph.

**Time Complexity:**

O(N+M),O(N + M),O(N+M),
where NNN is the number of intersections and MMM is the number of roads.

**Example Code Implementations:**

Below are the implementations in both C++ and Python using this approach.

`#include &lt;iostream&gt;
#include &lt;vector&gt;
#include &lt;algorithm&gt;
using namespace std;

int timer;
vector&lt;int&gt; tin, low;
vector&lt;bool&gt; visited, isArt;
vector&lt;vector&lt;int&gt;&gt; graph;

void dfs(int u, int parent) {
    visited[u] = true;
    tin[u] = low[u] = timer++;
    int children = 0;
    for (int v : graph[u]) {
        if (v == parent) continue;
        if (!visited[v]) {
            dfs(v, u);
            low[u] = min(low[u], low[v]);
            // For a non-root vertex, if no back edge exists from v or its descendants to u's ancestors
            if (parent != -1 &amp;&amp; low[v] &gt;= tin[u])
                isArt[u] = true;
            children++;
        } else {
            low[u] = min(low[u], tin[v]);
        }
    }
    // Special case for root
    if (parent == -1 &amp;&amp; children &gt; 1)
        isArt[u] = true;
}

int main() {
    int n, m;
    cin &gt;&gt; n &gt;&gt; m;
    graph.assign(n + 1, vector&lt;int&gt;());
    tin.assign(n + 1, -1);
    low.assign(n + 1, -1);
    visited.assign(n + 1, false);
    isArt.assign(n + 1, false);
    timer = 0;

    for (int i = 0; i &lt; m; i++) {
        int u, v;
        cin &gt;&gt; u &gt;&gt; v;
        graph[u].push_back(v);
        graph[v].push_back(u);
    }

    // Run DFS for every component (graph is assumed connected,
    // but this covers any disconnected components)
    for (int i = 1; i &lt;= n; i++) {
        if (!visited[i])
            dfs(i, -1);
    }

    vector&lt;int&gt; result;
    for (int i = 1; i &lt;= n; i++) {
        if (isArt[i])
            result.push_back(i);
    }

    cout &lt;&lt; result.size() &lt;&lt; "\n";
    sort(result.begin(), result.end());
    for (int v : result)
        cout &lt;&lt; v &lt;&lt; "\n";
    return 0;
}
